Who You Are

As an IT Developer Intern, your responsibilities include, but are not limited to:


Assist in designing, developing, and coding programs to enhance system functionality.
Support and troubleshoot existing systems under guidance from senior developers.
Collaborate with the team to perform unit and acceptance testing for new and existing applications.
Work alongside stakeholders to help identify and resolve technical issues, including debugging and performance profiling.
Learn and apply best practices for application optimization to improve system performance.
Apply agile development methodologies and industry best practices.
Contribute to team discussions by sharing ideas, asking questions, and supporting colleagues.
Follow established departmental standards and guidelines for development.


